# wc

> Count lines, words, or bytes
> More information: https://ss64.com/osx/wc.html

- Count lines in file:

`wc -l {file some description}`

- Count words in file:

`wc -w {file some description}`

- Count characters (bytes) in file:

`wc -c {file some description}`

- Count characters in file (taking multi-byte character sets into account):

`wc -m {file some description}`

- Use stdin to count lines, words and characters (bytes) in that order:

`{string some description: find .} | wc`
